commit.message: Add few more drain implementations

Rename flush to drain.

Add a law that any non-default definition should be extensionally
the same as default one.

Adding 'flush' method

`mapMaybe (const Nothing)` is often a constant map, and being able to provide a short-cut is useful (you may think it's never used, but consider `dropMissing` in `Data.Map.Merge.Strict`).

commit.message:
Bump version. Remove witherable-class.

The witherable-class package is removed because the
breaking change in witherable would cause the breaking change in
witherable-class as well.

As witherable-class is deprecated, now is a good moment to remove it.

Making WitherableWithIndex depend on FilterableWithIndex

This is a natural extension, and it's nice not to pollute your codebase with unnecessary assumptions to have access to the functionality.
